Pre-Game Insights: The Springboks are big favorites heading into their semifinal against England in Paris on Sunday NZT.
England lock Maro Itoje said, 'We’re not talking about a team that’s never lost. We’re not talking about a team that is without fault. They are a good team. But so are we.'
England has made to it the semifinals again, for the sixth time in 10 editions.
South Africa’s only loss in five World Cup meetings with England came in a pool game in 2003.
England has tinkered with its lineup, freshening the pack with two changes as lock George Martin comes in for just his ninth cap and prop Joe Marler is recalled to give more ballast in the scrum.
